.TH MIRROR 1 "25 Dec 2005" "@PACKAGE_VERSION@" "@PACKAGE_NAME@ utils"

.SH NAME
mirror \- mirror the files from the list on standard input

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B mirror
[
.IR OPTIONS
]

.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBmirror\fR copies the files it gets from standard input to the directory
specified with the \-b option. This script \fIimplements\fR the backup policy. 
.PP
If a file already exists in the backup directory it will be moved and
will get a suffix. This suffix is of the form: '+DD.HH:MM'. 

.SH OPTIONS
.TP 
.B \-b backupdir
Alternate backup directory. Defaults to /vol/backup/`hostname`.
.TP
.B \-k keyfile
Encrypt the files when backing up using the contents of keyfile as
an encryption key.
.TP
.B \-z
Gzip the contents of the files while backing up.
.TP
.B \-N
Dry-run, don't touch the filesystem, but echo what you want to do.
.TP
.B \-h
Short help message.

.SH FILES
/vol/backup/`hostname`, or the directory specified with \-b, root of
the backup file system.

.SH SEE ALSO
diff(1), hist(1), yesterday(1), rdup(8)
